  "prompt": "What universities does W&T offshore recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "W&T Offshore, a prominent company in the oil and gas industry, actively recruits new graduates to support its diverse operations. While specific recruitment strategies can evolve, here's an overview based on available information up to October 2023:\n\n### **Target Universities**\n\nW&T Offshore tends to recruit from a variety of universities, particularly those known for strong programs in engineering, geosciences, business, and related fields. Some of the universities they often consider include:\n\n- **Texas A&M University**\n- **University of Texas at Austin**\n- **Rice University**\n- **University of Houston**\n- **Louisiana State University**\n- **Oklahoma University**\n- **University of Louisiana at Lafayette**\n- **Southern Methodist University**\n- **North Carolina State University**\n\nThese institutions are recognized for their robust engineering and technical programs, aligning well with the industry needs of W&T Offshore.\n\n### **Preferred Majors and Fields of Study**\n\nW&T Offshore typically looks for graduates with degrees in areas that support their operations in exploration, production, and services. Key majors include:\n\n- **Petroleum Engineering**\n- **Mechanical Engineering**\n- **Chemical Engineering**\n- **Electrical Engineering**\n- **Civil Engineering**\n- **Geosciences (Geology, Geophysics)**\n- **Environmental Engineering**\n- **Computer Science and Information Technology**\n- **Business Administration and Management**\n- **Finance and Accounting**\n- **Supply Chain Management**\n- **Human Resources**\n\n### **Additional Considerations**\n\n- **Internships and Co-op Experience:** Candidates with relevant internship or co-op experience in the oil and gas sector may have an advantage.\n- **Technical Skills:** Proficiency in industry-specific software, data analysis, and project management tools is often valued.\n- **Soft Skills:** Strong communication, teamwork, and problem-solving abilities are essential in the collaborative environment of W&T Offshore.\n\n### **How to Stay Informed**\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information on recruitment:\n\n1. **Visit the [W&T Offshore Careers Page](https://www.wtoffshore.com/careers/):** This section typically lists current job openings, internship opportunities, and information about the recruitment process.\n2. **Attend Career Fairs:** W&T Offshore often participates in university career fairs, especially at the institutions mentioned above.\n3. **Connect on LinkedIn:** Following W&T Offshore on LinkedIn can provide updates on job postings and company news.\n4. **Contact Recruitment Representatives:** Reach out directly to the company\u2019s HR or recruitment team for personalized guidance.\n\nBy targeting universities with strong programs in relevant fields and seeking candidates with the appropriate technical and soft skills, W&T Offshore aims to build a talented and capable workforce to drive its operations forward.",
